52	12	1	Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly grease an 8-inch square baking dish.	\N	\N
53	12	2	Arrange apple slices evenly in the prepared baking dish. Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon, and salt into a bowl. Cut in butter using a pastry blender, or 2 knives, until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal; sprinkle over apples.	\N	\N
54	12	3	Bake in the preheated oven until topping is golden, 40 to 45 minutes. Cool slightly before serving.	\N	\N
